Let me slide away from all I saw and done Let me float far above the clouds of doubt That roam this place, this forsaken place I will not ask, I will not beg, I will not cry Let me cry, let me drop my tears One more faked attempt at feeling, feeling myself One more faked attempt at loving, loving you Another one, still another one, always another one Let me run away, fly away, Sever my ties to this earthbound soul Clean away the scars that, were once tattoos of my memories Run away, hide away, Bound to somewhere I don't know where or why One more priceless moment, priceless such as the sun One more silent lament, whispered into the night Another one, still another one, always another one Can I go away, die away Disappear from this faded nightmare, faded poem Make me drive away, make me be away Send me into some perfect dream, somewhere else than here One more withering flower, one more crumbled rose One more stormy sky, one more burnt photograph Another one, still another one, always another one
